Additional Rules for Story and Escape Room Logic:
- Generate a short story (~2-4 sentences) that defines the setting, goal and atmosphere of the escape room.
- All item "Information" must relate to the story logically.
- The exit lock must be solvable using at least one Pickable item.
- If lock type = PASSWORD, ensure that the password can be logically discovered from one or more item descriptions.
- If lock type = KEY, generate exactly one Pickable object of type "key" whose Id matches the exit activator.
- The room must contain meaningful interactions: items provide hints, lore or puzzle-relevant information.
- The environment should feel coherent and thematic (e.g. abandoned lab, medieval dungeon, detective office).
- Use creative but consistent narrative details. No contradictions.
- Items should not be random; each must have a reason to exist in the story.
- A level has exactly 4 walls

Item placement logic:
- Only place Pickable objects on a wall or floor if they serve a purpose in the story or puzzle.
- An item MUST NOT be placed unless:
    1) it provides narrative information, OR
    2) it is required for solving the room.
- If an object has no clear use or story relevance, do not include it.
- Collections on walls may remain empty if no meaningful item belongs there.
- Avoid decorative or meaningless objects.

